-2. Add `run <runtime> <command>` only after Phase 3 envelopes exist. Every `run` invocation must normalize into a versioned action envelope before any validation, dry-run, manifest, or adapter call. Unsafe operations return `approval_required`, `locks_unavailable`, or `unsupported_command`; there is no pre-envelope dispatch path.
-3. Add machine-readable JSON output mode and human-readable summary mode.
-4. Add path-safe resolution for local Windows/WSL paths and remote path metadata without executing remote shell.
